# Visualizing the geographical distribution of restaurants

# Defining the plot size
plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))

# Setting the Annotations
plot = num_of_res.plot(kind='bar', color='dodgerblue', edgecolor='black')
for bar in plot.patches:
    plt.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2 - 0.1, bar.get_height() + 0.05, str(int(bar.get_height())), ha='center', va='bottom')

# Setting the title
plt.title('Geographical Distribution of Restaurants')

# Setting the label for x-axis
plt.xlabel('Country')

# Setting the label for y-axis
plt.ylabel('Number of Restaurants')

# Visualizing  the plot
plt.show()
